### Base64-URL Encoding and Decoding with Supabase SSR

Source: https://context7.com/supabase/ssr/llms.txt

Provides RFC 4648 compliant Base64-URL encoding and decoding functions for safe cookie value storage. It handles Unicode characters correctly and ensures cookie compliance. The library automatically applies this encoding to cookie values when configured.

```typescript
import { stringToBase64URL, stringFromBase64URL } from '@supabase/ssr'

// Encode string to Base64-URL (no padding, URL-safe)
const original = 'Hello, 世界! Special chars: +/='
const encoded = stringToBase64URL(original)
console.log(encoded) // 'SGVsbG8sIOS4lueVjCEgU3BlY2lhbCBjaGFyczogKy89'

// Decode back to original string
const decoded = stringFromBase64URL(encoded)
console.log(decoded === original) // true

// Handles Unicode correctly
const unicode = '{"user":"José","role":"admin","emoji":"🚀"}'
const encodedUnicode = stringToBase64URL(unicode)
const decodedUnicode = stringFromBase64URL(encodedUnicode)
console.log(decodedUnicode === unicode) // true

// Library automatically applies base64url encoding to cookie values
const supabase = createBrowserClient(
  'https://your-project.supabase.co',
  'your-anon-key',
  {
    cookieEncoding: 'base64url' // default, ensures cookie RFC compliance
  }
)

// Use 'raw' encoding only for backward compatibility (not recommended)
const legacyClient = createBrowserClient(
  'https://your-project.supabase.co',
  'your-anon-key',
  {
    cookieEncoding: 'raw' // legacy mode, may cause issues with special chars
  }
)
```

